# SPDX-License-Identifier: Apache-2.0 WITH LLVM-exception
#
# .gitignore for the VS Code extension at editors/vscode/.
#
# T1 contributed: `language-configuration.json`, `syntaxes/*.json`, the
# top-level package.json — all source-controlled and hand-curated.
#
# T8 added the `treesitter/` subdirectory carrying the TypeScript
# extension shell (extension.ts / highlight-provider.ts / legend.ts /
# tsconfig.json). Its generated artefacts MUST stay out of the repo:
#
#   - `node_modules/` is the npm install output.
#   - `package-lock.json` IS committed for runner-version byte-
#     stability (same precedent as test/tooling/textmate/).
#   - Compiled `.js` / `.js.map` files live next to their `.ts`
#     sources (outDir=rootDir=. in tsconfig.json) for the folder-
#     drop install model, but they're generated by `npm run compile`
#     and must regenerate cleanly from the .ts.
#   - `tree-sitter-nsl.wasm` is built by `cd grammars/treesitter &&
#     npx tree-sitter build-wasm --docker` and either copied here
#     for local-install or downloaded as a CI workflow artefact;
#     never committed per Clarifications session 2026-05-05 Q2 →
#     Option C.
#
# See specs/010-t8-tree-sitter-grammar/research.md §1 (CLI pin) and
# §2 (WASM lifecycle) for the rationale.

node_modules/
treesitter/*.js
treesitter/*.js.map
treesitter/tree-sitter-nsl.wasm
